Given, x + a + b + c = 0<br><br>$$\left| {\matrix{
   {x + a} &amp; b &amp; c  \cr 
   a &amp; {x + b} &amp; c  \cr 
   a &amp; b &amp; {x + c}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>$$ = \left| {\matrix{
   {x + a + b + c} &amp; b &amp; c  \cr 
   {x + a + b + c} &amp; {x + b} &amp; c  \cr 
   {x + a + b + c} &amp; b &amp; {x + c}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>[by $${C_1} \to {C_1} + {C_2} + {C_3}$$]<br><br>$$ = (x + a + b + c)\left| {\matrix{
   1 &amp; b &amp; c  \cr 
   1 &amp; {x + b} &amp; c  \cr 
   1 &amp; b &amp; {x + c}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>[x + a + b + c common from C<sub>1</sub>] = 0<br><br>[$$\because$$ x + a + b + c = 0]

Since, the vectors are coplanar.<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $$\left| {\matrix{
   \alpha  &amp; \alpha  &amp; \gamma   \cr 
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 1  \cr 
   \gamma  &amp; \gamma  &amp; \beta   \cr 

 } } \right| = 0$$<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\alpha$$($$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) $$-$$ $$\alpha$$(0 $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) + $$\gamma$$(0 $$-$$ $$\gamma$$) = 0<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\alpha$$$$\beta$$ $$-$$ $$\alpha$$$$\gamma$$ + $$\alpha$$$$\gamma$$ $$-$$ $$\gamma$$<sup>2</sup> = 0<br><br>$$\Rightarrow$$ $$\gamma$$<sup>2</sup> = $$\alpha$$$$\beta$$<br><br>Hence, $$\gamma$$ is GM of $$\alpha$$ and $$\beta$$.

We have,<br><br>$$y = {\cos ^ - }\left( {{{2x} \over {1 + {x^2}}}} \right) = {\pi  \over 2} - {\sin ^{ - 1}}\left( {{{2x} \over {1 + {x^2}}}} \right)$$<br><br>$$ = \left\{ \matrix{
  \left[ {{\pi  \over 2} - (2{{\tan }^{ - 1}}x)} \right],\left| x \right| &lt; 1 \hfill \cr 
  \left[ {{\pi  \over 2} - (\pi  - 2{{\tan }^{ - 1}}x)} \right],x &gt; 1 \hfill \cr 
  \left[ {{\pi  \over 2} - ( - \pi  - 2{{\tan }^{ - 1}}x)} \right],x &lt;  - 1 \hfill \cr}  \right.$$<br><br>$$ = \left\{ \matrix{
  {\pi  \over 2} - 2{\tan ^{ - 1}}x,\left| x \right| &lt; 1 \hfill \cr 
   - {\pi  \over 2} + 2{\tan ^{ - 1}}x,x &gt; 1 \hfill \cr 
  {{3\pi } \over 2} + 2{\tan ^{ - 1}}x,x &lt;  - 1 \hfill \cr}  \right.$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ $${{dy} \over {dx}} = \left\{ \matrix{
  {{ - 2} \over {1 + {x^2}}},\left| x \right| &lt; 1 \hfill \cr 
  {2 \over {1 + {x^2}}},x &gt; 1 \hfill \cr 
  {2 \over {1 + {x^2}}},x &lt;  - 1 \hfill \cr}  \right.$$
